       The   following   example,   invoked   with   the   string
       /home/sms/personal/mail sets the environment variable NAME
       to  the  file  named  mail  and  the  environment variable
       MYMAILPATH to the string /home/sms/personal.   NAME=`base-
       name  $HOME/personal/mail`  MYMAILPATH=`dirname $HOME/per-
       sonal/mail`

       This  shell   procedure,   invoked   with   the   argument
       /usr/src/bin/cat.c,  compiles the named file and moves the
       output to cat in the current directory:  cc  $1  mv  a.out
       `basename $1 .c`

